          <p>Once upon a time, in a galaxy far, far away, there were three planets called Decimal, Binary, and Hexadecimal. Each planet had its own way of representing numbers. On the Decimal planet, the people used numbers like we do, but on the Binary planet, they used only 1s and 0s, and on the Hexadecimal planet, they used a combination of numbers and letters.
          <p>For example, the number 46 meant forty-six on the Decimal planet, but on the Binary planet, it was 101110, and on the Hexadecimal planet, it was 2E.</p>
          <p><br></p>
          </p>

          <img class="wappler-type-picture mb-3 mr-3 float-left" width="320">

          <p>For centuries, these planets rarely interacted with each other. But one day, a super bad guy appeared with a powerful secret weapon. He wanted to use this weapon to destroy everything in the universe. The people from the three planets knew they had to work together to defeat him. But they had a problem: Their number systems were so different, they couldn't communicate with each other.
          <p><br></p>
          <p>That's when a superhero named Alan appeared. He was multilingual and knew how to convert between different number representations. To help the people from the three planets communicate with each other, he taught them how to convert their numbers to decimals.</p>
          <p><br></p><img class="wappler-type-picture mb-3 mr-3 float-left" width="320">
          <p>Alan explained that just like in decimal numbers, each digit corresponds to a power of 10, in binary numbers, each digit corresponds to a power of 2. To convert from binary to decimal, they just needed to multiply each digit by its corresponding power of 2 and add up the results. For example, to convert the binary number 110 to a decimal number, they just needed to do 1 x 2² + 1 x 2¹ + 0 x 2⁰, which equals 6.</p>
          <p><br></p>
          </p>



