          <img class="wappler-type-picture mb-3 mr-3 float-right" width="320">
          <p>Alan also explained that people on the Hexadecimal planet used numbers 0-9 and letters A-F to represent decimal numbers 0-16. To convert from hexadecimal to decimal, they only needed to multiply each digit by its corresponding power of 16 and add up the results. For example, to convert the hexadecimal number C3 to a decimal number, since C represents 12 in decimal, they just needed to do 12 x 16¹ + 3 x 16⁰, which equals 195.</p>
